    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. you say it was a \"failure\" because of the instability, but some analysts argue that the intervention actually prevented a massive humanitarian catastrophe and a slaughter in Benghazi. wouldn't you say that preventing a mass casualty event makes the intervention a success on a moral and stabilization level, even if the long-term politics are messy?",
